<br>
>>Locust Plague: (2,400 DoT in 60 seconds, Mana: 500, Cast Time= 5 Seconds, Recast= Instant, LOW FIZZLE, Stacks with all but Winged Death).<br>
<br>
The swarm DoT upgrade I was referring to before.  Very nice.<br>
<br>
<br>
>>Renewal: OUTDOOR ONLY/Only where Tree Illusion Works, 96% Resurection, Summons Player to body and gives illusion TREE for 5 minutes (uncancelable). Mana= 1200, Reagent: Acorn of Life (Sold at some Druid's Guilds for ~300pp, or 'Quest').<br>
<br>
Very interesting.  Although I doubt we would ever get a res spell.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
>>Ro's Pure Flame: (1,600 DoT in 54 seconds, -200 Attack, -60 FR (no stack with RFS), Mana: 350, Cast Time= 5 seconds, Recast=Instant, LOW FIZZLE, Stacks with all but Breath of Ro).<br>
<br>
A second DoT upgrade to the fire line, with some mixing of the RFS debuff.  I like it.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
>>Tunare's Tearful Veil: (GROUP, Effect: Protection from debuffing for duration of spell. Mana: 500, Duration: 5 minutes, Cast Time= 3 seconds, Recast=10 minutes). <br>
<br>
Now THIS is new.  Uniquely druidic as well, and undoubtedly something that would give a druid a place on any raid anywhere.  <br>
