<br>
Renewal.. I would have to make the spell give both "Resurection Effects" and a new -buff/debuff called "Sapling Growth"...  In order to keep people from just camping out, and removing the treeform.. that "Sapling Growth" would have to Re-Cast TREEFORM/ROOT every tick.. so that the player would be stuck with the penalty of treeform for the duration of the buff/debuff (5 minutes).<br>
<br>
Could also make the "Acorn of Life" unstackable, 10.0 wt, and LORE.<br>
<br>
=-=-=<br>
<br>
Now, if Druids get resurection.. I am sure Shaman's will also complain unless they get it too... so here is a Shaman-Version of Resurection..<br>
<br>
<b>Gathering of Spirits</b><br>
Level:Shaman (55-60?)<br>
Mana: 1200<br>
Casting Time: 5.0 seconds.<br>
Recast Time: Instant<br>
Reagent: Spiritual Elixer (Made with Alchemy: Cost to make ~300pp, Skill~100 = 70% sucess. LORE)<br>
INDOOR ONLY<br>
<br>
Added Effects: "Resurection Effects" for standard Time... Also gets "Weak Spirit" (Zero HP/MANA regeneration, SNARE for 5 minutes).<br>
<br>
I also kind of like this spell...but it would be a miracle if Verant would go for it.<br>
<br>
<b>Spiritual Shield:</b> (Shaman, (55-60),GROUP, Effect: A Death durring this buff, will result in no exp loss (Re-appear at bind with 20% HP, 0% mana, All Buffs gone).  Mana=500, Casting Time= 3.0 seconds, Recast = 15 minutes, Duration = 5 minutes.<br>
<br>
Perhaps it also needs a Alchemy created "reagent".. Something expensive....<br>
